\v 13 “But woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you shut the kingdom of heaven before people! For you do not enter, nor permit those wanting to go in\ef + \fr 23:13 \ft ﻿*Here the present tense has been translated as voluntative (“wanting to go in”) \ef* to enter.\f + \fr 23:13 \ft The most important Greek manuscripts omit v. \xt 14 \ft , “Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you devour widows’ houses and for show you pray long prayers! Therefore you will receive the greater condemnation.” \f*
