\c 25
\s1 The Parable of the Ten Virgins
\m 
\v 1  “Then the kingdom of heaven may be compared to ten virgins who took their lamps \add and\add*\ef + \fr 25:1 \ft ﻿*Here “\add and\add*” is supplied because the previous participle (“took”) has been translated as a finite verb \ef* went out to meet the bridegroom. 
